**who —** The Electron Neutrino — A nearly massless, chargeless lepton that interacts only via the weak force — so weakly that trillions pass through you each second unnoticed.

**what —** A nearly massless, chargeless lepton that interacts only via the weak force — so weakly that trillions pass through you each second unnoticed.

**where —** ATM · The Atom  Framework inputs: the Standard Model & atomic/nuclear physics  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** BALANCES BETA DECAY. Emitted (as its antiparticle) whenever a neutron decays, carrying off energy and conserving the books. The ghost particle that lets the weak force do its bookkeeping.

**how —** BALANCES BETA DECAY. Emitted (as its antiparticle) whenever a neutron decays, carrying off energy and conserving the books. The ghost particle that lets the weak force do its bookkeeping.

